  JOHANNESBURG - Basic Education Minister Angie Motshekga says most schools, affected by the floods, will reopen by Friday. Plans are in place to repair those more severely damaged. WATCH | Basic Education Minister inspects schools affected by KZN floods More than 600 schools in KZN were damaged, affecting 320,000 pupils. Motshekga says a plan is in place to accommodate those children without schools. Courtesy #DStv403